e worker processes based on CPU count</span>\n<span class=\"pl-k\">const</span> <span class=\"pl-c1\">workers</span> <span class=\"pl-k\">=</span> <span class=\"pl-c1\">Math</span>.<span class=\"pl-c1\">min</span>(<span class=\"pl-en\">cpuCount</span>(), <span class=\"pl-c1\">4</span>);\n<span class=\"pl-c1\">console</span>.<span class=\"pl-c1\">log</span>(<span class=\"pl-s\"><span class=\"pl-pds\">`</span>Starting ${<span class=\"pl-smi\">workers</span>} worker processes<span class=\"pl-pds\">`</span></span>);\n</code></pre>\n<h5>Example:</h5><pre><code class=\"language-ts\"><span class=\"pl-c\">// Performance monitoring</span>\n<span class=\"pl-k\">const</span> <span class=\"pl-c1\">cores</span> <span class=\"pl-k\">=</span> <span class=\"pl-en\">cpuCount</span>();\n<span class=\"pl-c1\">console</span>.<span class=\"pl-c1\">log</span>(<span class=\"pl-s\"><span class=\"pl-pds\">`</span>System has ${<span class=\"pl-smi\">cores</span>} CPU cores available<span class=\"pl-pds\">`</span></span>);\n</code></pre>\n<h5>Since:</h5><p>1.0.0</p>\n<h5>See:</h5><p><a href=\"https://nodejs.org/api/os.html#os_os_cpus\">https://nodejs.org/api/os.html#os_os_cpus</a> - Node.js os.cpus() documentation</p>\n"},"sources":[{"fileName":"packages/node-utils/src/system/os.ts","fullFileName":"/home/runner/work/fe-tools/fe-tools/utils/packages/node-utils/src/system/os.ts","line":70,"character":0,"url":"https://github.com/MichealWayne/fe-tools/blob/3274750/utils/packages/node-utils/src/system/os.ts#L70"}],"parentId":2184}],"is":{"declaration":true},"location":{"query":"node-utils/src.Function.cpuCount","hash":""},"text":{},"parentId":965}
